HEADWORD: Odin
<hw>O"din</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[Icel. <?/;
prob.akin to E. <ets>wood</ets>, a. See <er>Wednesday</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Northern Mythol.)</fld> <def>The supreme deity of the
Scandinavians; -- the same as <er>Woden</er>, of the German
tribes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There in the Temple, carved in wood,⟦br⟧
The image of great <qex>Odin</qex> stood.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

